pie: mannikim's personal image editor
===
provides `pie`, the image editor and `pcp`, a color picker program

features
- uses farbfeld as the image format. see https://tools.suckless.org/farbfeld
- stdin/stdout
- area selection
- simple terminal ui
- <2k loc

usage
---
use `pie -h` for usage

pie uses stderr for displaying a simple tui. this allows the program to
display text-based information without implementing font loading & rendering
to the program

pcp takes no arguments and always returns the selected color in the stdout

configuring
---
configure pie by editing the source code and recompiling

build
---
building requires a c99 compiler, libm, GLFW and GLEW

the compiler needs to support `__attribute__((always_inline))`, or you can
change the definition of the `ALWAYS_INLINE` macro in `common.h`

building

    make

install

    make install

